quotes.quote: Who you with, what you claim, I was payin' mama's rent when I was turnin' 17
My ex asked me where you moving, I said onto better things, yeah
I might be too strung out on compliments, overdosed on confidence
They know, they know, they know
Tuck my napkin in my shirt 'cause I'm just mobbin' like that
Tension, between us just like picket fences
Harder buildin' trust from a distance
Then their phone doesn't ring when they got everything
Looking back on it at least my pride is intact
